ce:section.ce:para:
In the current study, we investigated the effect of CNDs on the wettability (contact angles
, θ
) of an oil-wet carbonate reservoir by measuring the contact angle of the rock-CO2-brine systems as a function of temperature (20 °C- 80 °C) and pressure (14.3–3000 psi). The objective is to pre-treat the reservoir with CNDs to shift the wettability more towards the water-wet, feasibly, this will improve the CO2 geo-storage, as well it can promote their security containment in the depleted reservoir of the Saudi Arabian carbonate formation. The temperature and pressure conditions are chosen as representative of the downhole condition of Saudi Arabian carbonate reservoirs.
